<inglise> 97/16/EC: Council Decision of 20 December 1996 setting up an Employment and Labour Market Committee </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU OTSUS 97/16/E&Uuml;, millega asutatakse t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ive- ja t&ouml;&ouml;turukomitee 20. detsember 1996 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 145 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 145, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust (1) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the European Council, at its recent meetings, confirmed that the fight against unemployment and the effort to achieve equal opportunities were the paramount tasks for the Community and its Member States; </inglise>
<eesti> Euroopa &Uuml;lemkogu on oma hiljutistel istungj&auml;rkudel kinnitanud, et t&ouml;&ouml;tusevastane v&otilde;itlus ja p&uuml;&uuml;dlused tagada v&otilde;rdsed v&otilde;imalused on &uuml;henduse ja selle liikmesriikide t&auml;htsaimad &uuml;lesanded; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, at its meeting on 9 and 10 December 1994 in Essen, the European Council identified priority areas for action to overcome structural employment problems; whereas it requested each Member State to incorporate these recommendations into a multiannual programme; whereas it invited the Council in the field of Labour and Social Affairs and Economic and Financial Affairs and the Commission to keep close track of employment trends, to monitor the relevant policies of the Member States and to report annually to the European Council on further progress on the employment market; whereas it asked at its meeting on 15 and 16 December 1995 in Madrid to establish as soon as possible the practical monitoring systems, including a system of common indicators; </inglise>
<eesti> Essenis 9. ja 10. detsembril 1994 toimunud istungj&auml;rgul m&auml;&auml;ras Euroopa &Uuml;lemkogu kindlaks esmat&auml;htsad tegevusvaldkonnad t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivega seotud struktuuriliste probleemide lahendamiseks; ta palus k&otilde;ikidel liikmesriikidel l&uuml;litada need soovitused mitmeaastasesse programmi; Euroopa &Uuml;lemkogu palus t&ouml;&ouml;- ja sotsiaalvaldkonna n&otilde;ukogul, majandus- ja rahandusvaldkonna n&otilde;ukogul ja komisjonil t&auml;helepanelikult j&auml;lgida t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ive arengusuundi ja liikmesriikide asjakohast poliitikat ning esitada Euroopa &Uuml;lemkogule igal aastal aruanne t&ouml;&ouml;turul toimunud arengu kohta; oma 15. ja 16. detsembril 1995 Madridis peetud istungj&auml;rgul n&otilde;udis Euroopa &Uuml;lemkogu, et tuleb v&otilde;imalikult kiiresti luua vajalikud j&auml;relevalves&uuml;steemid, sealhulgas &uuml;histe n&auml;itajate s&uuml;steem; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the European Council at its meeting in Madrid urged Member States to apply in the framework of their multiannual employment programmes measures with particular emphasis on those categories requiring special attention, such as young people seeking their first job, the long-term unemployed and unemployed women; </inglise>
<eesti> Madridi istungj&auml;rgul soovitas Euroopa &Uuml;lemkogu liikmesriikidel tungivalt v&otilde;tta mitmeaastaste t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveprogrammide raames meetmeid, mis on eelk&otilde;ige suunatud erit&auml;helepanu vajavatele kategooriatele nagu esimest t&ouml;&ouml;kohta otsivad noored, pikaajaliselt t&ouml;&ouml;tud ja t&ouml;&ouml;tud naised; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Council in the field of Economic and Financial Affairs is assisted by the Economic Policy Committee set up by Council Decision 74/122/EEC (2), in order to contribute to the coordination of the short and mid-term economic policies; </inglise>
<eesti> majandus- ja rahandusvaldkonna n&otilde;ukogu abistab n&otilde;ukogu otsusega 74/122/EM&Uuml; (2) asutatud majanduspoliitika komitee, et aidata kaasa l&uuml;hiajalise ja keskmise t&auml;htajaga majanduspoliitika koosk&otilde;lastamisele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Council in the field of Labour and Social Affairs has been assisted, thus far, by an ad hoc Working Party of the Representatives of Ministers for Labour and Employment set up on 27 March 1995; </inglise>
<eesti> t&ouml;&ouml;- ja sotsiaalvaldkonna n&otilde;ukogu on seni abistanud 27. m&auml;rtsil 1995 t&ouml;&ouml;k&uuml;simustega tegelevate ministrite esindajatest moodustatud ajutine t&ouml;&ouml;r&uuml;hm; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to ensure the continued success of the Community's strategy for employment and to facilitate the practical implementation of the employment monitoring procedure decided on in Essen, the European Council at its meeting in Madrid in December 1995 felt that it was necessary to establish, as soon as possible, a stable structure to assist the Council in the field of employment; </inglise>
<eesti> 1995. aasta detsembris Madridis kohtunud Euroopa &Uuml;lemkogu leidis, et &uuml;henduse t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivestrateegia j&auml;tkuva edukuse tagamiseks ja Essenis vastuv&otilde;etud t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ive j&auml;relevalvemenetluse praktilise rakendamise h&otilde;lbustamiseks on vaja v&otilde;imalikult kiiresti luua p&uuml;siv struktuur, mis abistaks n&otilde;ukogu t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ive valdkonnas; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is now appropriate for the Council to decide to set up an Employment and Labour Market Committee in the light of decisions taken by successive European Councils following publication of the White Paper on Growth, competitiveness and employment of 1993; Whereas it is important to associate the social partners with future work in this field; </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogul on praegu asjakohane teha otsus t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ive- ja t&ouml;&ouml;turukomitee asutamise kohta, pidades silmas otsuseid, mis on tehtud Euroopa &Uuml;lemkogu j&auml;rjestikustel istungj&auml;rkudel p&auml;rast majanduskasvu, konkurentsiv&otilde;imet ja t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivet k&auml;sitleva valge raamatu avaldamist 1993. aastal; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the setting up of the Committee is without prejudice to the respective competences of Member States and the Community in the fields covered by the work of the Committee and without prejudice to Article 151 of the Treaty as regards preparing the work of the Council, </inglise>
<eesti> on oluline kaasata t&ouml;&ouml;suhte pooled edaspidi selles valdkonnas tehtavasse t&ouml;&ouml;sse; komitee asutamine ei piira liikmesriikide ja &uuml;henduse p&auml;devust komitee tegevusvaldkondades ega ka asutamislepingu artikli 151 kohaldamist seoses n&otilde;ukogu t&ouml;&ouml; ettevalmistamisega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS DECIDED AS FOLLOWS: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD J&Auml;RGMISE OTSUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> An Employment and Labour Market Committee (hereinafter referred to as 'the Committee') is hereby set up to assist the Council in carrying out its responsibilities in these fields. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevaga asutatakse t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ive- ja t&ouml;&ouml;turukomitee (edaspidi "komitee"), mis aitab n&otilde;ukogul t&auml;ita k&otilde;nealuste valdkondadega seotud &uuml;lesandeid. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Within the terms of the policy priorities laid down by the Council, the Committee shall, inter alia with regard to the multiannual programmes of the Member States and to the common system of indicators to be established: </inglise>
<eesti> Komiteel tuleb n&otilde;ukogu poolt s&auml;testatud tegevusprioriteete silmas pidades ning muu hulgas seoses liikmesriikide mitmeaastaste programmide ja loodava &uuml;histe n&auml;itajate s&uuml;steemiga t&auml;ita j&auml;rgmisi &uuml;lesandeid: </eesti>
<inglise> - keep close track of employment trends for men and women in the Community and monitor the Member States' employment and labour market policies, </inglise>
<eesti> - j&auml;lgida t&auml;helepanelikult meeste ja naiste t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ive arengusuundi &uuml;henduses ning liikmesriikide t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ive- ja t&ouml;&ouml;turupoliitikat, </eesti>
<inglise> - facilitate exchanges of information and experience between Member States and with the Commission in these fields. </inglise>
<eesti> - h&otilde;lbustada liikmesriikide omavahelist ning liikmesriikide ja komisjoni vahelist info- ja kogemustevahetust k&otilde;nealustes valdkondades. </eesti>
<inglise> The Committee shall prepare reports and proposals for the Council on these questions. </inglise>
<eesti> Komitee koostab n&otilde;ukogule nende k&uuml;simuste kohta aruandeid ja ettepanekuid. </eesti>
<inglise> It may, on its own initiative, undertake work within its area of competence. </inglise>
<eesti> Ta v&otilde;ib omal algatusel teha t&ouml;&ouml;d oma p&auml;devusvaldkonnas. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The Committee shall work as far as necessary in cooperation with other relevant bodies, in particular the Economic Policy Committee. </inglise>
<eesti> Komitee teeb vajadust m&ouml;&ouml;da koost&ouml;&ouml;d teiste asjaomaste organitega, eelk&otilde;ige majanduspoliitika komiteega. </eesti>
<inglise> It will also maintain an appropriate liaison with the Standing Committee on Employment. </inglise>
<eesti> Komitee hoiab vajalikul m&auml;&auml;ral kontakti ka alalise t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivekomiteega. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> The Committee shall consist of two representatives appointed by each Member State and two representatives of the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> Komiteesse kuulub igast liikmesriigist kaks liikmesriigi nimetatud esindajat ning kaks komisjoni esindajat. </eesti>
<inglise> These representatives may be assisted by two alternates. </inglise>
<eesti> Esindajaid v&otilde;ivad abistada kaks asendusliiget. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The Committee shall elect its chairman from among the representatives of the Member States for a non-renewable term of two years. </inglise>
<eesti> Komitee valib oma esimehe liikmesriikide esindajate hulgast kaheaastaseks ametiajaks, mida ei saa pikendada. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall provide the analytical and organizational support for the Committee. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon pakub komiteele anal&uuml;&uuml;tilist ja organisatsioonilist tuge. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall liaise with the General Secretariat of the Council with regard to the holding of meetings. </inglise>
<eesti> Koosolekute korraldamisel teeb komisjon koost&ouml;&ouml;d n&otilde;ukogu peasekretariaadiga. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The Committee shall establish its own rules of procedure. </inglise>
<eesti> Komitee kehtestab ise oma t&ouml;&ouml;korra. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Meetings on the Committee shall be convened by the chairman, either on his own initiative or at the request of at least half of the members of the Committee. </inglise>
<eesti> Komitee koosolekud kutsub kokku komitee esimees kas omal algatusel v&otilde;i v&auml;hemalt poolte komiteeliikmete taotlusel. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 20 December 1996. </inglise>
